# .harness/env — harness configuration, sourced by scripts/poll-and-dispatch.sh
#
# This file is committed so a team's checkouts share defaults. The per-feature
# COUNTER files in .harness/ (feedback-rounds-*, local-check-attempts-*,
# last-main-sha) are runtime state and are gitignored — never commit those.

# How many features the harness works in parallel.
#   1 = single worktree, FIFO (recommended default for a single developer).
#   2+ = bounded parallelism; each feature gets its own worktree (more disk).
MAX_WORKTREES=1

# Which PRD branches this harness claims (git refspec glob; * = one component).
#   prd/<your-slug>/*  = per-dev (default): only your own PRDs, your own quota.
#   prd/*/*            = shared pool: all harnesses race; atomic rename is safe.
# Leave unset to use the per-dev default derived from your git email.
# WATCH_PATTERN=prd/your-slug/*

# Headless permission posture for the `claude -p` skill subprocesses. A headless
# session can't show a permission prompt, so it needs a posture or tool calls are
# denied and the step falsely STUCKs. Default (set in the dispatcher) is:
#   CLAUDE_PERM_ARGS=( --permission-mode auto )
# classifier-gated, prompt-free, fail-safe (repeated blocks -> abort -> STUCK).
# Uncomment to override when `auto` isn't available or wanted — e.g. a Bedrock/
# Vertex-backed CLI (auto is Anthropic-API only), a claude older than
# --permission-mode, or to skip the classifier entirely inside the worktree:
# CLAUDE_PERM_ARGS=( --dangerously-skip-permissions )
